HEADWORD: Doubtable
<hw>Doubt"a*ble</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[OF.
<ets>doutable</ets>, L. <ets>dubitabilis</ets>, from
<ets>dubitare</ets>. Cf. <er>Dubitable</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>Capable of being doubted; questionable.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Worthy of being feared; redoubtable.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Doubtance</ent>⟦br⟧
